  "text": "To select the best ISSR primers for A. flaccida in Step 1, each amplified locus was evaluated according to the presence (1) or absence (0) of the DNA fragments (band). Based on the binary matrix obtained, the discriminatory power of ISSR primers was evaluated using three parameters: (i) polymorphism information content (PIC), (ii) marker index (MI), and (iii) resolving power (RP). The PIC for each ISSR loci was computed as PICi = 2ƒ i (1 − f i ); where PICi is the polymorphic information content of the marker 'i,' ƒ i is the frequency of the amplified locus (band present), and 1-ƒ i is the frequency of the null allele [CITATION_1] . MI was calculated as described in Varshney et al. [CITATION_2] : MI = PIC x EMR, where EMR is \"the effective multiplex ratio (E) and is defined as the product of the total number of loci per primer (n) and the fraction of polymorphic loci (β) (EMR = n. β).\"",
